A_350 - Some transactions are extremely safe to carry out (e.g. walking to a nearby shop and buying a fruit with money) while others are not (e.g. when operating in certain areas using IT tools and from far away). Depending on how we relate to carrying out the transaction, the final result of the &ldquo;purchase&rdquo; could be more or less improving. For example, buying newly developed dynamite without absolutely knowing how to use it could lead to disastrous results (assuming for example that it doesn't explode when you light the fuse, but with a scream...).